Application: Help Desk Ticket Tracker
  Description: Track support tickets from submission to resolution
Id: 9d81658f-b642-437f-8f39-ffe31faa7701

--- Identity ---

Users authenticate with stub
Scopes are "tickets.view", "tickets.create", "tickets.manage", and "tickets.admin"

--- Roles ---

A "customer" has "tickets.view" and "tickets.create"
A "support agent" has "tickets.view", "tickets.create", and "tickets.manage"
A "support manager" has "tickets.view", "tickets.create", "tickets.manage", and "tickets.admin"

--- Content ---

Content called "tickets":
  Each ticket has a title which is text, required
  Each ticket has a description which is text, required
  Each ticket has a priority which is one of: "low", "medium", "high", "critical"
  Each ticket has a category which is one of: "bug", "feature request", "question", "account issue"
  Each ticket has a submitted by which is text, required, defaults to `User.Name`
  Each ticket has an assigned to which is text
  Each ticket has a created at which is automatic, defaults to `now`
  Each ticket has a ticket lifecycle which is state:
    ticket lifecycle starts as open
    ticket lifecycle can also be in progress, waiting on customer, resolved, or closed
    open can become in progress if the user has tickets.manage
      success shows toast `ticket.title + " is now in progress"`
    in progress can become waiting on customer if the user has tickets.manage
      success shows toast "Ticket moved to waiting on customer"
    waiting on customer can become in progress if the user has tickets.create
      success shows toast "Ticket reopened"
    in progress can become resolved if the user has tickets.manage
      success shows banner `ticket.title + " resolved"` dismiss after 10 seconds
    resolved can become closed if the user has tickets.admin
      success shows toast "Ticket closed"
    resolved can become in progress if the user has tickets.create
      success shows toast "Ticket reopened from resolved"
  Anyone with "tickets.view" can view tickets
  Anyone with "tickets.create" can create tickets
  Anyone with "tickets.manage" can update tickets
  Anyone with "tickets.admin" can delete tickets

Content called "comments":
  Each comment has a ticket which references tickets, required
  Each comment has an author which is text, required, defaults to `User.Name`
  Each comment has a body which is text, required
  Each comment has a posted at which is automatic, defaults to `now`
  Anyone with "tickets.view" can view comments
  Anyone with "tickets.create" can create comments

--- User Stories ---

As a customer, I want to submit a support ticket
  so that I can get help with my issue:
    Show a page called "Submit Ticket"
    Accept input for title, description, priority, and category
    Create the ticket as open

As a support agent, I want to see all open tickets
  so that I can work on resolving them:
    Show a page called "Ticket Queue"
    Display a table of tickets with columns: title, priority, category, ticket lifecycle, assigned to, created at
    Highlight rows where `priority == "critical" || priority == "high"`
    Allow filtering by ticket lifecycle, priority, and category
    Allow searching by title or description
    For each ticket, show actions:
      "Start Work" transitions ticket lifecycle to in progress if available, hide otherwise
      "Wait on Customer" transitions ticket lifecycle to waiting on customer if available, hide otherwise
      "Resolve" transitions ticket lifecycle to resolved if available, hide otherwise
      "Reopen" transitions ticket lifecycle to in progress if available, hide otherwise
      "Close" transitions ticket lifecycle to closed if available, hide otherwise
    This table subscribes to tickets changes

As a support manager, I want to see ticket metrics
  so that I can monitor team performance:
    Show a page called "Support Dashboard"
    Display total ticket count with open vs resolved breakdown
    Display total comment count

--- Navigation ---

Navigation bar:
  "Queue" links to "Ticket Queue" visible to agent, manager
  "Submit" links to "Submit Ticket" visible to all
  "Dashboard" links to "Support Dashboard" visible to manager

Stream ticket updates at /api/v1/stream
